  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "7:1-10 Ezra went from Babylon to Jerusalem, for the good of his country. The king was kind to him; he granted all his requests, whatever Ezra desired to enable him to serve his country. When he went, many went with him; he obtained favour from his king, by the Divine favour. Every creature is that to us, which God makes it to be. We must see the hand of God in the events that befal us, and acknowledge him with thankfulness.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A ready scribe - Or, \"a ready writer\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 45:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The professional scribe was well known in Egypt from an early date (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 39:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " note); and under David and his successors \"scribes\" were attached to the court as the king's secretaries (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 8:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 20:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 12:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.). It was scarcely, however, until the time of the captivity that the class to which Ezra belonged arose. The \"scribes\" of this time, and of later Jewish history, were students, interpreters, and copiers of the Law (see the marginal references and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 8:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). They retained the knowledge of the old dialect, which was being rapidly superseded by a new one. The emphatic application of the title \"the scribe\" to Ezra marks the high honor in which the office was now held. Its glories eclipsed those of the priesthood.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The hand of the Lord ... upon him - The use of this phrase in a good sense is rare elsewhere (compare 1 Kings 18:46), but is a favorite one with both Ezra and Nehemiah (see the marginal references; Nehemiah 2:8, Nehemiah 2:18). ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The hand of the Lord ... upon him - The use of this phrase in a good sense is rare elsewhere (compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 18:46",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "), but is a favorite one with both Ezra and Nehemiah (see the marginal references; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Nehemiah 2:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Nehemiah 2:18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
