  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 7.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - The same six classes are here mentioned as furnishing colonists under Ezra which, according to the earlier narrative (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 2:70",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), had accompanied Zerubbabel. The order in which the classes are mentioned is nearly, but not quite, the same. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "In",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "the seventh year of Artaxerxes.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " This is the emphatic clause of the verse; Ezra's main object in the section being to give the exact date of his journey. As Artaxerxes began to reign in  ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "date",
        "text": "B.C. 464",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Clinton, F. H., vol. 2. p. 380, note b), his seventh year would be  ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "date",
        "text": "B.C. 458",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Ezra 7:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
